text: Hey all, for the Flumine <https://github.com/betcode-org/flumine/blob/04d607e1d749a2dbaa8297bbf74c062990867a6b/examples/strategies/marketrecorder.py|marketrecorder>. Other than passing the name of the bucket as a string in the context kwarg dict is there anything else that needs to be done to ensure the recorded markets are moved to the bucket? At the moment the files are recorded and zipped but aren't being uploaded to the bucket despite me passing the bucket name. the files is then automatically deleted. I have the correct IAM role assigned to the EC2 instance to allow it to access S3 so I am uncertain what the issue is.
